Real DevOps Scripts
boto3 — AWS automation:

import boto3

# Stop all EC2 instances
ec2 = boto3.client('ec2', region_name='us-east-2')
instances = ec2.describe_instances()
for r in instances['Reservations']:
    for i in r['Instances']:
        ec2.stop_instances(InstanceIds=[i['InstanceId']])
        print(f"Stopped: {i['InstanceId']}")

subprocess — run shell commands:

import subprocess

# Run kubectl command from Python
result = subprocess.run(
    ['kubectl', 'get', 'pods', '-n', 'default'],
    capture_output=True,
    text=True
)
print(result.stdout)

requests — call APIs:

import requests

# Call your app health endpoint
response = requests.get('http://myapp.com/health')
if response.status_code == 200:
    print("App healthy ✅")
else:
    print("App unhealthy ❌")

pyyaml — parse K8s yaml:

import yaml

# Read Deployment.yaml
